<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4783] ConcurrentModificationException when stopping</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4783</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The exception below happens in the karaf itests but originates in felix.&lt;br/&gt;
The problem is in org.apache.felix.gogo.runtime.CommandProcessorImpl.stop .&lt;br/&gt;
It iterates over the sessions in a foreach loop and removes the session during the iteration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I propose to do the remove at the end in one clear call.&lt;br/&gt;
This should go into gogo runtime 0.14.1. Unfortunately there is no version for it in jira.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;14:31:55,602 | ERROR | Felix                                              | Error stopping bundle.&lt;br/&gt;
java.util.ConcurrentModificationException&lt;br/&gt;
